  "prompt": "Are there any TV series similar to How to Get Away with Murder?",
  "response": "Yes, if you enjoyed \"How to Get Away with Murder,\" you might like the following TV series, which share similar themes of legal drama, suspense, and intricate plots:\n\n1. **Scandal** - Created by Shonda Rhimes, this series follows a crisis management expert and her team as they handle scandalous political situations while confronting their own personal drama.\n\n2. **The Good Wife** - This legal and political drama follows a woman who returns to her career as a lawyer after her husband's public scandal and political corruption lands him in jail.\n\n3. **The Good Fight** - A spin-off of \"The Good Wife,\" this series continues to explore complex legal battles and social issues through the eyes of a seasoned lawyer.\n\n4. **Suits** - Focused on a top Manhattan law firm, this series combines humor and drama as brilliant but unlicensed lawyer Mike Ross teams up with Harvey Specter to take on high-profile cases.\n\n5. **Grey's Anatomy** - Another Shonda Rhimes show, this medical drama involves complex characters dealing with both personal and professional crises, featuring intricate relationships and plot twists.\n\n6. **How to Get Away with Murder: The After Show** - A follow-up that delves into character insights and elaborate narrative elements discussed by the cast and creators.\n\n7. **Damien** - A psychological thriller that follows a man who discovers his connection to the Antichrist, facing moral dilemmas and dark plots.\n\n8. **Dead to Me** - This dark comedy involves a widow and her friendship with an eccentric woman, with plenty of twists that lead to a gripping narrative.\n\n9. **The Following** - Though more of a crime thriller, it involves a former FBI agent trying to track down a serial killer whose cult of followers commit complex murders.\n\n10. **Your Honor** - A legal drama that revolves around a respected judge whose life becomes complicated when his son is involved in a hit-and-run that connects to a mob family.\n\nEach of these shows has strong character development, gripping storylines, and a blend of drama that you might find compelling!",
